WEBVTT

00:00:04.220 --> 00:00:05.760
What's right for you

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:08.420
doesn't necessarily work for the next person.

00:00:08.420 --> 00:00:10.760
<v Audio Descriptions>Toast with different levels of darkness.

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.760
Customization isn't always just

00:00:12.760 --> 00:00:14.740
the question of preference though

00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:16.600
Sometimes it's a necessity.

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:19.080
<v Audio Descriptions>Two men are sitting with a toaster between them.

00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:21.380
<v Audio Descriptions>One of the men turns the toaster dial.

00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:23.640
Being able to adjust the text is crucial

00:00:23.640 --> 00:00:26.000
for people with low vision and dyslexia.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.760
<v Audio Descriptions>A woman puts on glasses to read a website on her laptop.

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:32.100
<v Audio Descriptions>The woman is squinting at the website

00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:34.660
<v Audio Descriptions>with small text and an unusual font.

00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:39.000
Properly coded websites and applications allow the text to be customized.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:43.560
For example, to change its size, spacing, font and colors

00:00:43.560 --> 00:00:45.800
without loss of functions or clarity.

00:00:45.840 --> 00:00:48.480
<v Audio Descriptions>The woman uses the web browsers settings

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.840
<v Audio Descriptions>to adjust the text size and style.

00:00:50.840 --> 00:00:54.460
<v Audio Descriptions>It appears more legible and the woman is relieved.

00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:56.280
<v Audio Descriptions>Cutback to the two men.

00:00:56.280 --> 00:00:59.500
<v Audio Descriptions>One of the men takes a piece of toast out of the toaster.

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:01.500
Web accessibility

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:04.400
Essential for some, useful for all.
